name: 1000BASE-EX
description: 1000BASE-EX is a non-standard but industry accepted term[31] to refer to Gigabit Ethernet transmission. It is very similar to 1000BASE-LX10 but achieves longer distances up to 40 km over a pair of single-mode fibers due to higher quality optics than a LX10, running on 1310 nm wavelength lasers.
